definitions.definition: A former inland county of England , partly absorbed into the erstwhile County of London in 1889; finally abolished in 1965 and absorbed mainly into Greater London , the south-west corner of the county becoming Spelthorne Borough and included in Surrey .
The central of the three historical counties of Jamaica , bordered by the counties of Cornwall in the west and Surrey in the east ; named for the English county.
